children.title: Gentleman Prefer Perms
children.description:
The young men of the 1950's became more hair conscious and started thinking in terms of hair styling , including permanent waves, seen here at the Hounslow salon of Leonard Pountney, London, Middlesex, England.
This young man has his hair set in perming rods, which need to be left to set.
October 1953

children.title: Paris Dogs are Chic
children.description:
Au Chien Elegant - Dog grooming in Paris for the pampered pet. The groomer starts by removing the dog's fur around the paws with electric grooming equipment. The dog sits patiently while this is done.
October 1951

children.title: A barber's shop: the central figure is a man seated, swathed in a sheet while a boy on the left applies tongs to his hair, which a man on the right is combing; two men on the left admire their freshly curled hair in the mirror; on the extreme right a barber shaves a man to whom next stands a man who stanches a cut on his cheek with a towel; in the left-hand foreground a seated customer reads a newspaper with a concerned expression. Coloured etching with aquatint by T. Rowlandson after W.H. Bunbury.

children.title:
Frisörskan 2 september 1965

En äldre dam sitter på en stol inne i en salong. Hon har ett skyddsförkläde på sig. Bakom henne står en hårfrisörskeelev som är i färd med att kamma den äldre damens hår. Bilden är tagen genom spegeln som står framför dem. Fotografens arm skymtar i spegeln. En frisörstol syns även i spegeln.

children.title: Hår Kläder : Accessoarer och tillbehör Motivkategori : Föremål Smycken
children.description: Smycke. Hårnålar,  från 1800-talets sista årtionden. Hårnålar användes för att hålla omfångsrika frisyrer och hattar på plats. Förermål ur Nordiska museets samlingar, fotograferade inför utställningen Smycken med öppningsdatum 2012-09-14.

children.description: A man is sitting on a chair, while another man, obviously a barber, is lathering his beard. Three men are watching the scene.

children.title: Yul Brynners of Kent 1957
children.description:
For over 25 men in the village of Adisham , Kent , a walk down the village street means running a gauntlet of guffaws and ribald laughter - for the men are completely bald - from choice . Each had a '' Yul Brynner '' and had his hair shaved off . It all started one night in the Moor's Head , the local pub where the men foregather . Bob Bailey , a husky 34-year-old miner , said idly to his friend , Cyril Theobald , I wouldn't mind having a Yul Brynner haircut , you know ...''   '' Bet you ten fags you daren't , '' said Cyril . '' You ' re on , '' said Bob . There and then , the local amateur barber , 59-year old Llewellyn Jones , was called into action , and in less time than it used to take bob to comb his locks , he hadn't any .
The last man to have his hair cut off - so far - is Bill Henderson, also a miner "I felt embarrassed down the pit" he said " I felt the odd man out, as if I was the one with a peculiar hairstyle!" With his hair half gone , Bill Henderson has aged , and looks far from happy . 
1957

children.title: Hula - Hula Haircut
children.description:
Do you feel bored while waiting to have a haircut? and do you get tired of thumbing through week-old magazines as you sit in expectation of the cry 'Next , gent , please ?
Meet a hairdresser who has banished all this by substituting hula hula girls for dour-faced male assistants and given his salon a south seas decor .  Man behind this Hula Hula idea is Mr Leonard Poutney , of Hounslow , Middlesex.  With his attractive girl assistants wearing grass skirts , topless jumpers , yes , and even garlands of flowers round there pretty necks , it's little wonder that business for him is booming .
1956

children.title: Barbers - 1953
children.description:
Style is the thing at the Barbers - 1953_x000D_
The young men of today are becoming more hair conscious and are thinking in terms of hair styling , including permanent waving at the Hounslow salon of Leonard Poutney_x000D_
_x000D_Gordon Spenser , South of England amateur Latin American ballroom dancing champion has a pompadour .  18 months ago he was a short back and sides man ._x000D_

children.title: Dutch barber shaving a young man, 18th C
children.description:
Lettering: J. Gole fe. et ex.
The barber wears a pointed hat; his shaving instruments hang in a pouch at his side and he holds a razor in his right hand. The young man holds a plate under his chin to catch the soapy drips.

children.title: Four images showing women wearing different styles of fashionable wigs.
children.description: Lettering: This a fashionable wig! _ why its like a horses main it makes me quite a fright. ; Mr. Friz assures me this is the true botanical wig intended to be worn, by the Blue Stocking Club _ I declare I look as wise as Doctor Humbrum himself. ; Well this is the thing to be sure _ nature itself, in very curl. ; How do you like, mem, my light summer wig _ I'm told it will be all the rage.

children.title: A country barber shaving a farmer; another farmer looks
children.description:
Lettering: A country barbers shop.
A country barbers shop. A country barber shaving a farmer; another farmer looks into a mirror while he stanches the cut on his face; in the right-hand background a second barber dresses a man's hair. Coloured engraving.
